                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d279">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.91262/124: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Ambassador in Germany (<persName type="to">Dodd</persName>)</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-08-21T17:00:00-04:00"
                            >August 21, 1933—5 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>102. Department’s No. 99, August 19, 1 p.m. Representative <hi rend="italic"
                        >Chicago Daily News</hi> informs me Mowrer is leaving Berlin tomorrow. <hi
                        rend="italic">Daily News</hi> expresses concern for Mowrer’s personal safety
                    through Germany and also for that of his wife and children remaining for the
                    present in Berlin. Fears are also expressed in connection with his property.</p>
                <p>Please exercise your own judgment and take whatever steps seem to be
                    desirable.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Phillips</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
